3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with communication protocols in a network. 
4. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper mentions the optical network unit (ONU) and the drop-point device, which could be related to hardware architecture. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper involves simulations of bursty traffic models, which could be related to computational engineering.
